docs.abstract: Emboldened by #MeToo, entry-level workers in the entertainment industry have banded together for more money and better behavior from their bosses.
docs.snippet: Emboldened by #MeToo, entry-level workers in the entertainment industry have banded together for more money and better behavior from their bosses.
docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Kiran Subramaniam was in her mid-20s when she was hired as an assistant at ICM, one of the Big Four talent agencies in Los Angeles. The job paid $12 an hour. One day, her boss, an agent, tossed a small package at her head after she had placed it on his desk in a way he didn’t like. She ducked, but it grazed her face. When she threatened to quit, he apologized, saying he had thrown the box as a joke. Ms. Subramaniam decided to stay — like a “sad sack,” she said.

headline.main: Hollywood Assistants Are Fed Up and No Longer Afraid to Say So
headline.print_headline: Hollywood Assistants Look to Write a New Script

docs.abstract: Mr. Sanders edged out his competitors in The Des Moines Register/CNN poll released on Friday, the first significant survey from Iowa in nearly two months.
docs.snippet: Mr. Sanders edged out his competitors in The Des Moines Register/CNN poll released on Friday, the first significant survey from Iowa in nearly two months.
docs.lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Bernie Sanders edged ahead of his Democratic rivals in Iowa, affirming his resurgence less than four weeks before next month’s caucuses, according to a new poll from The Des Moines Register and CNN.

headline.main: Bernie Sanders Leads Tight Race in New Iowa Poll
headline.print_headline: In New Poll, Sanders Moves Ahead of Democratic Rivals in Iowa

docs.abstract: The find in a Nevada desert revealed an intestine inside a creature that looks like a worm made of a stack of ice cream cones.
docs.snippet: The find in a Nevada desert revealed an intestine inside a creature that looks like a worm made of a stack of ice cream cones.
docs.lead_paragraph: They say you should trust your gut, which is what Emmy Smith did when she went hunting for fossils in 2016. Dr. Smith, a field geologist, had a hunch she would find something interesting at a site north of Pahrump, Nev., and she did. But what her gut hadn’t told her was that some of those fossils would turn out to contain the oldest known animal guts on the planet.

headline.main: Fossil Reveals Earth’s Oldest Known Animal Guts
headline.print_headline: Intestinal Front-Numbers: In Nevada, Finding a Jackpot Of Very Old Guts

docs.abstract: The president, addressing supporters in Ohio, said that he had killed a “bloodthirsty terror” and slammed Democrats for seeking to restrain his power to make war.
docs.snippet: The president, addressing supporters in Ohio, said that he had killed a “bloodthirsty terror” and slammed Democrats for seeking to restrain his power to make war.
docs.lead_paragraph: TOLEDO, Ohio — President Trump opened his re-election year in the Midwest on Thursday, hoping to translate his confrontation with Iran into strength on the campaign trail as he boasted about killing the head of its elite security forces and derided Democrats for seeking to restrain his power to go to war.

headline.main: At First Rally of Election Year, Trump Boasts About Strike on Iranian General
headline.print_headline: Flexing Military Might As Trump Visits Ohio, An Election Linchpin

docs.abstract: As evidence emerged that an Iranian missile may have felled a jetliner, causing the death of 63 Canadians, journalists pressed Justin Trudeau over whether President Trump should bear any of the blame.
docs.snippet: As evidence emerged that an Iranian missile may have felled a jetliner, causing the death of 63 Canadians, journalists pressed Justin Trudeau over whether President Trump should bear any of the blame.
docs.lead_paragraph: MONTREAL — New evidence indicating that an Iranian surface-to-air missile caused the plane crash this week that killed 63 Canadians is likely to undermine Canada’s already acrimonious relationship with Iran. But the disaster also threatens to damage Ottawa’s crucial but fraught partnership with Washington.

headline.main: Evidence That Plane Was Shot Down in Iran May Upset U.S.-Canada Relations
headline.print_headline: In Canada, Debate on How Much Blame Should Fall on the U.S.
